This paper deals with improving citation impact measurements, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as the paper discusses the use of Web of Science (WoS) for data collection. The second likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the paper deals with the analysis of citation data. The third likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computational Geometry), as the paper uses statistical analysis to improve citation impact measurements. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper deals with the analysis of data to improve prediction. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper deals with the analysis of citation data and the impact of various factors on citation impact.
